The remains of actor Ernest Asuzu would be interred on April 13 in Imo State. The Nation gathered that the late actor’s remains will be interred after a scheduled ceremony slated for three days in April 2021. In a chat with Asuzu’s widow, Amina Asuzu, it was revealed that the burial rites will kick-off with a wake-keep ceremony slated for April 12. The wake-keep ceremony will be followed by the burial which is scheduled to hold at the Asuzu’s compound in Ndiejezie village, Arondizuogu, Imo State. The late actor slumped and died in January 2021.